quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  12,30,"Certain women that were in the city said, 'The Governor's wife has been soliciting her page; he smote her heart with love; we see her in manifest error"
  12,31,"When she heard their sly whispers, she sent to them, and made ready for them a repast, then she gave to each one of them a knife. 'Come forth, attend to them,' she said. And when they saw him, they so admired him that they cut their hands, saying, 'God save us! This is no mortal; he is no other but a noble angel"
  12,32,"So now you see, she said. 'This is he you blamed me for. Yes, I solicited him, but he abstained. Yet if he will not do what I command him, he shall be imprisoned, and be one of the humbled"
  12,33,"He said, 'My Lord, prison is dearer to me than that they call me to; yet if Thou turnest not from me their guile, then I shall yearn towards them, and so become one of the ignorant"
  12,34,"So his Lord answered him, and He turned away from him their guile; surely He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing"
  12,35,"Then it seemed good to them, after they had seen the signs, that they should imprison him for a while"